<h2>Dropdown — the single-select droplist</h2>
<p>The <strong>dropdown</strong> is the canonical concrete member of the <a href="/blocks/droplist/">droplist family</a>: a button-triggered, non-filtering, single-select listbox. It exists at three altitudes of the trait language — raw HTML substrate, named custom-element preset, and TypeScript trait composition — all of which produce the same composition. As a form-associated custom element, it participates in <code>&lt;form&gt;</code> submission, <code>FormData</code>, reset, and validity exactly like the native <code>&lt;select&gt;</code>.</p>

<h3>Trait selection at a glance</h3>
<p>The dropdown's identity is fixed by these trait selections. Structural picks are <strong>local</strong> (an author cannot change them via props or ambient intent); behavioral picks are this component's <em>stance</em> and remain overridable by an ambient <code>droplistIntent</code>:</p>
<we-data-table>
<table class="data-table">
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Trait</th><th>Dimension</th><th>Value</th><th>Kind</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><a href="/intents/selection/">Selection</a></td><td><code>model</code></td><td><code>single</code>, follows focus</td><td><strong>structural</strong></td></tr>
    <tr><td><a href="/intents/type-ahead/">Type-Ahead</a></td><td>presence</td><td>on (mutually exclusive with filter)</td><td><strong>structural</strong></td></tr>
    <tr><td><a href="/intents/focus-delegation/">Focus Delegation</a></td><td><code>strategy</code></td><td><code>virtual</code> (<code>aria-activedescendant</code>)</td><td>behavioral</td></tr>
    <tr><td><a href="/intents/anchor/">Anchor</a></td><td>placement / collision</td><td><code>bottom-start</code> / <code>flip,resize</code></td><td>behavioral</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
</we-data-table>

<h3>Altitude 1 — HTML, explicit behaviors (the substrate)</h3>
<p>Each attribute is one trait; the attribute <em>value</em> is the trait selection. This is what the substrate looks like at the DOM level, with hardcoded items for clarity. The JSX mirror is near-identity — only the inline comments (<code>&lt;!-- --&gt;</code> → <code>{/* */}</code>) and the two-root wrapper (a <code>&lt;&gt;</code> fragment) differ:</p>
{{ sourceToggle("dropdown-substrate") }}
{% highlight "html" %}
<button aria-haspopup="listbox" anchor="country-list"
        commandfor="country-list" command="toggle-popover">Country</button>

<ul id="country-list" role="listbox"
    focus-delegation="strategy=virtual"     <!-- behavioral; may default from ambient intent -->
    selection="model=single"                <!-- STRUCTURAL: always local -->
    type-ahead
    anchored="placement=bottom-start;collision=flip,resize"
    popover>
  <li role="option" composite-descendant data-value="ar">Argentina</li>
  <li role="option" composite-descendant data-value="au">Australia</li>
</ul>
{% endhighlight %}
